<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN347">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>uṇpōṉ ṟāṉaṟuṅ kaḷḷi ṉiṭaccila</l>
<l>nāviṭaip paḵṟēr kōlac civanta</l>
<l>voḷiṟoḷ vāṭak kuḻaintapain tumpai</l>
<l>yeṟintilai muṟinta katuvāy vēliṉ</l>
<l>maṇanāṟu mārpiṉ maṟappō rakutai</l>
<l>kuṇṭunīr varaippiṟ kūṭa laṉṉa</l>
<l>kuvaiyiruṅ kūntal varumulai cēppa</l>
<l>mārpiṉ maṟappō rālai ceppa</l>
<l>veṉṉā vatuko ṟāṉē <supplied>cēnta</supplied></l>
<l>viḷaṅkuṟu parāraiya vāyiṉum vēntar</l>
<l>viṉainavil yāṉai piṇippa</l>
<l>vērtuḷaṅ kiṉanam mūruṇ maraṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Like Kūṭal within the bounds of the deep water</l>
<l>of Akutai of bold battle, [his] chest fragrant with scent,</l>
<l>with a blunt spear the leaf [tip] of which is broken after throwing [it],</l>
<l>with fresh Tumpai that is withered so that [its] resplendent light fades(?),</l>
<l>when the beauties sought out by the teeth on the tongue turned red,</l>
<l>few, as the eater himself plut [them] with the fragrant toddy?????????????,</l>
<l>while [she] with coming breasts [and] massed dark tress dwells [there]</l>
<l>what will become of it?</l>
<l>Even if [their] large trunks flourish(?), when kings</l>
<l>tie work-trained elephants [to them]</l>
<l>the trees inside our village will break at the roots.</l>
</lg>
    </div>
